GITHUB Class -2

TOPIC: GITHUB & BITBUCKET


Launch one instance ---------> name: GITHUB ---------> kernerl 6.1--------> t3.micro---------->keypair ------------> MY-SEC-GRP-------->
--------> 8gb ebs volume------------> launch instance & connect

* yum install git -y

https://github.com/pranay-devops666/microservices-project.git

lets clone this repository through SSH

difference between HTTPS & SSH is 

when we are going the push the code everytime it may ask credentials 
but in real time the credentials will won't ask to us because we will use SSH in real time

HTTPS  ---------> it may ask credentials every time when we are going to push the code
SSH    ---------> it won't ask credentials every time when we are going to push the code

for doing through ssh, we need to do generate ssh-key in ec2-instance

when we generate ssh-key in ec2-instance one public key & one private key will occur

now what we will do is taking the public-key and we will put it in github


* ssh-keygen        ---------------> command to generate ssh-key in ec2-instance
after giving the above command ec2-instance one public key & one private key will occur
it will be present in .ssh folder

[root@ip-172-31-26-214 ~]# ssh-keygen
