[root@ip-172-31-26-214 .ssh]#

here we need to take public key and open the id_rsa like below

[root@ip-172-31-26-214 .ssh]# cat id_rsa.pub
ssh-rsa  root@ip-172-31-26-214.ec2.internal
[root@ip-172-31-26-214 .ssh]# 

now go to github--------> go to settings ----------> on left side SSH & GPG Keys-----> open it--------> select new SSH key------->
name:my-ec2-key ---------> do paste that copied the key here--------> add shh-key----------> it will ask github account credentials-----> key has been added

it will not the credentials when this key has been present in github

now go to github and select any one of the repository-------> select code --------> select SSH link copy and give command like below

[root@ip-172-31-26-214 ~]# git clone git@github.com:pranay-devops666/microservices-project.git
